en:
The raw materials are noble and local: the quality ingredients are rigorously selected and come exclusively from short circuits.
The recipes are healthy and balanced: all the preparations are elaborated without additives or preservatives and can be kept at room temperature with a 2 year shelf life. The range of products remains traditional and family-oriented, while sometimes having a touch of originality. The taste is unaltered. Why add sugar or salt when you don't need it?
The jams are extra made with more than 55g of fruit for 100g of finished product.
Some forgotten products of yesteryear are used to titillate your taste buds, you will also discover daring mixtures of certain flavors.
The range of cookies (sweet and salty) represents essentially delicacies from the South of France.

On the markets, Elsa also proposes pancakes with organic chestnut flour, which she garnishes with her own jams for the sweet and salty ones, she selects quality raw materials from local producers (e.g.: pelardons, cooked ham, etc...)

Mystère Mijoté is a local artisanal cannery, where mysterious recipes are made with fruits and vegetables from Elsa's own agricultural production, wild harvesting and local producers.

Present on the markets of : St Etienne Vallée Française - Ste Croix Vallée Française - Holiday village of St Germain de Calberte (Le petit calbertois) - St Jean du Gard

On a regional and national scale: Presence on fairs, shows and theme markets.

For more information: contact by phone, facebook and e-mail.
